Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第十三集
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我們已經一起經歷了一段漫長的旅程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We've come a long way together,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.97,0:04:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我們深入了原子的內核\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}traveling from deep inside the heart of an atom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.28,0:05:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,抵達了宇宙的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}clear out to the cosmic horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,從時間的起源走到遙遠的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and from the beginning of time to the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是時候做一些實驗了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I think we're ready to perform an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.94,0:05:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,這不是那種在實驗室裏才能做的實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not the kind of experiment that requires a laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以在自己的腦海裏完成它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can do it in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,它稱之為"思想實驗"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's called a "thought experiment."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,選一顆星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pick a star--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.79,0:05:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我們的銀河系裏選上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}any one of the hundreds of billions of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這數以百億顆星星中的一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in our Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,其實銀河系也只不過是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which is just one galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,目前已知宇宙的上百億個星系中的一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}out of the hundred billion in the known universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆怎麼樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How about that star?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.63,0:05:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,或者是那一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Or that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,好 就是這顆吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Okay, this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,有幾十個行星和衛星圍繞著它旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's orbited by dozens of planets and moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,假設 其中的一顆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Suppose, on one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,上面有智能生物存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there lives an intelligent species,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,他們是這個行星裏上千萬種生命形式的一種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one the ten million life-forms on that planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,在這些智能生物中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and there's a subgroup of that species
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,有一小部分生物認為他們已經發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who believe they have it all figured out--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,這個世界就是宇宙的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their world is the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,這個宇宙為他們而造\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a universe made for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.16,0:06:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他們已經無所不知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that they know everything they need to know about it--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,擁有了圓滿的智慧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}their knowledge is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.47,0:06:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,你覺得他們的話可以當真嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How seriously would you take their claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的祖先就認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our ancestors believed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙是為他們而造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the universe was made for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,把人假定為世界的中心是很自然的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was natural to assume that we were at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,畢竟 太陽和其他的星星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After all, it looks like the Sun and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.35,0:06:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,看起來都圍繞著人類轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all revolve around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在還在說 太陽是"升"起來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We still speak of the Sun "rising."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.49,0:06:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,人類的語言 神話和夢想的體系結構\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The architecture of our language, myths and dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:06:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,是來自科學誕生前的時代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}comes from that pre-scientific age.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.70,0:07:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,在哥倫布出航發現新大陸前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is our planet as it was known then,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.07,0:07:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,人們都認為已經很瞭解這個星球了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just before Columbus set sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.74,0:07:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這是世界上第一個地球儀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This first globe of the Earth was cutting-edge
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,馬丁•貝海姆在1492年製造了這個當時是最前沿的產品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when Martin Behaim made it in 1492.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.71,0:07:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,和當時的其他人一樣 他認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like everyone else, he believed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這幅世界地理的拼圖已經完整無缺了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the jigsaw puzzle of geography was complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.88,0:07:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,上面有三個大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There were three continents...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,歐洲 非洲和亞洲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Europe, Africa and Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,三個大洲之間只有浩瀚的大洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and only the great world ocean in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,貝海姆地球儀上看不到北美洲與南美洲的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Behaim had no clue that North and South America even existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,人很容易自以為是 對不對\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's easy to feel smug, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,事實上 馬丁•貝海姆對他的世界的瞭解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, the fact is Martin Behaim knew infinitely more
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.70,0:07:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,對地球的瞭解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about his world, the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.81,0:07:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,遠遠勝過我們對於宇宙的瞭解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than we know about ours, the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,近代有一個關于謙虛的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A recent lesson in humility
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.04,0:07:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,可以很好的作為明證\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will serve to illustrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,1912年 維克托•赫斯進行了好幾次飛行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1912, Victor Hess made a series of voyages
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,他飛越了奧地利上空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the sky above Austria,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:07:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,發現了科學家們期待已久的東西…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and found the thing that scientists love best...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.59,0:08:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,一個神秘而無法理解的事件\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a mystery that defied understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,用傳統的科學無法解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in terms of conventional scientific wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,時至今日\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And even today,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.47,0:08:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,100年過去了 我們仍在苦苦搜尋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a century later, we are still searching
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.77,0:08:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,要為赫斯的發現找一個完整的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a complete explanation of what Hess found.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.48,0:08:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,當時有一種新的能量剛被發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A new kind of energy had recently been discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,輻射能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}radioactivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}也就是放射能
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.98,0:08:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,自然界中某種特定的元素會釋放出輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was given off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.45,0:08:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,比如鐳\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by certain elements, like radium.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,但空氣中也有輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it was also found in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.29,0:08:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,在遠離放射性岩石的地方也有輻射\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even far away from radioactive rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,它可說是無處不在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,這些奇怪的能量是從哪裏來的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Where did this strange energy come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.33,0:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,無人知曉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No one knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯推測它可能來自地球上空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hess suspected that it might come from above the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,為了驗證這個假設 他攜帶著輻射探測器\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To test his hypothesis, he carried radiation detectors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,飛向高空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}high into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他冒著乘坐氫氣球的風險\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}During a risky ascent in a hydrogen balloon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.64,0:08:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他到達了海拔超過3英里的高度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he attained an altitude of more than three miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.45,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,當他來到空氣稀薄 溫度寒冷的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When he reached the thin, cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,大氣層中部以上時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}upper half of the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他發現這裏的輻射值\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he found that the radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,比地面的要強2倍以上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was more than twice as strong as on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這些輻射一定是來自於更高處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The radiation must be coming from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,因此它在地面才會比較弱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's why its intensity was weaker on the ground--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,因為地球的大氣層吸收了大部分能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Earth's atmosphere was absorbing most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,有人認為這些輻射可能來自於太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some thought that the radiation might come from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.65,0:09:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,為了測試這個說法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To test that idea, Hess timed one of his ascents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.32,0:09:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯在一次日食時升上高空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to coincide with a solar eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他發現日食對輻射沒有任何影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But the eclipse had no effect on the radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯還發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hess also found that the radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,輻射在白天和晚上的強度是一樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was just as strong at night as in daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,這些輻射是來自於高空 但不是太陽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was coming from above, but not from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What Hess did not know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.21,0:10:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽風根本就沒有那麼快的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was that the solar wind doesn't move that quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 他憑著這個錯誤的理由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And so, for the wrong reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,做出了正確的結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he came to the right conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.88,0:10:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯發現了宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hess had discovered cosmic rays--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.95,0:10:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那些如陣雨一般在宇宙中交錯飛灑的亞原子粒子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}showers of subatomic particles that crisscross the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,它們以光速行進著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at literally the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒有地球大氣層的保護\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without the shielding effect of the Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,它們可致人死地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they would be lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,某些宇宙射線攜帶的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some cosmic rays can carry as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.57,0:10:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,與步槍中發射的子彈一樣強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a bullet fired from a rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,人類花了幾十年的時間追蹤宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would take decades to trace those cosmic rays
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,才發現它們那無法想像的恐怖死亡之面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}back to a death of unimaginable violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,赫斯在奧地利上空發現的宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The cosmic rays that Victor Hess detected
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.67,0:10:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,向科學家們提出了一個謎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the skies above Austria posed a mystery to scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的放射性礦物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Radioactivity in minerals on Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,比如鈾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like uranium ore--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的放射性來自於原子的裂變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}comes from the disintegration of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.10,0:11:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,但宇宙射線具有不同的性質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But cosmic rays were of a different nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.27,0:11:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的能量更強大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They were far more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.74,0:11:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,比當時赫斯的世界中任何一種已知物質都要強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than anything known in Hess's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.25,0:11:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家們探索了20年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Scientists wondered for two decades
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.42,0:11:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,想要知道是什麼東西產生了宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what could possibly produce cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.08,0:11:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,下面介紹弗裏茨•茲威基\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Enter Fritz Zwicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.69,0:11:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,一個你從沒聽說過的最聰明的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the most brilliant man you've never heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.79,0:11:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,1933年 他和一個同事發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1933, he and a colleague discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.86,0:11:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,某些恆星會突然變得非常耀眼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that some stars flare up to become as bright
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.63,0:11:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,亮度就和它們所在的星系差不多並延續好幾周\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as their entire galaxy for a few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.87,0:11:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,然後又會黯淡下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before fading out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.30,0:11:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,弗裏茨•茲威基是世界上第一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fritz Zwicky was the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.80,0:11:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,瞭解這個現象的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to understand what just happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.37,0:11:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,他正確的推測出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He correctly surmised that this is the way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,這代表著一顆大質量恆星的死亡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a massive star dies-- it blows
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.58,0:11:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,爆炸將恆星的物質拋入太空\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its guts out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.65,0:11:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,他把這種恆星的死亡稱為"超新星"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He called this kind of stellar death a "supernova"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,並推測這顆垂死的恆星將會坍縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and predicted that the dying star would shrink
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,從100萬英里的直徑收縮為10英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from about a million miles across to only ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,恆星的殘骸密度如此之大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This corpse would be so dense
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,一粒米那麼大的物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that a single grain of it would weigh as much
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.03,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,就會和埃及大金字塔一樣重\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the Great Pyramid in Egypt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.77,0:12:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它將幾乎由\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would consist almost entirely
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.87,0:12:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,一種叫中子的亞原子粒子組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of subatomic particles called neutrons,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.21,0:12:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,所以他也將這種奇異的物體稱為"中子星"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so he named these bizarre objects "neutron stars."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.58,0:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,自從茲威基預測這個現象存在後的35年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And 35 years after Zwicky predicted their existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.91,0:12:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家開始找到它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}astronomers began to find them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.82,0:12:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我們將它們稱為"脈衝星"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We call them "pulsars"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.75,0:12:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,它們在快速自轉的同時會發射出有規律的脈衝電波信號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when they spin rapidly and emit regular pulses of radio energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.39,0:12:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,超新星與中子星都能發出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Supernovas and neutron stars could account
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,大量的宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a wide range of cosmic rays,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.39,0:12:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但不是能量最強的那種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but not the most energetic ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.93,0:12:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,現在的科學還不能很好解釋這種現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing yet known to science
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.63,0:12:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不過沒事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can explain them, and we're fine with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是我愛科學的原因之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's one of the things I love about science,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.60,0:12:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我們從不假裝自己知道所有的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we don't have to pretend we have all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.24,0:12:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,茲威基還認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Zwicky also came up with the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.81,0:12:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,星系的重力會讓它四周的空間結構發生彎曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the gravity of a galaxy warps the fabric
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.78,0:12:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,就像放大鏡一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of space around it, to act like a lens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,從而讓在它後面的其它星系的光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This distorts and magnifies light
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.18,0:12:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在穿過這個星系時發生扭曲並放大的效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from any other galaxy lying directly behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.62,0:12:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因此地球上的天文學家們在觀測 具有相同距離的遙遠星系時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, astronomers on Earth would see multiple images
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,會看到有多重圖像出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of that same distant galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像遊樂園的哈哈鏡效果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}deformed, as in a funhouse mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他做出這一預測40年後 人們才開始發現這一現象真實存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}40 years after this prediction, we started finding them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.97,0:13:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,茲威基在1930年代還有另一個發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And Zwicky made yet another discovery back in the 1930s.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,在觀測後發座星系團時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}While studying the Coma Cluster of galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他注意到星團的移動方式很有意思\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he noticed something funny about the way they moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.05,0:13:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,它的移動速度很快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The galaxies were going way too fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.28,0:13:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在這麼快的速度下 這個星團早就該飛散了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so fast that they should've been flying apart from each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,因為在所有這些星系中的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because all the stars in all those galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的引力太小 無法維繫整個星團的穩定\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had far too little gravity to hold the cluster together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,茲威基認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Zwicky thought
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.13,0:13:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,一定有某種力量將它們維繫在一起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that something else must be binding them to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.73,0:13:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這看不見找不著的神秘部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That mysterious missing component
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它的重量至少是星團中所有的恆星總重的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would have to weigh something like 50 times as much
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,50倍以上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the stars themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.50,0:13:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但沒人對他的超前見解感興趣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But no one paid much attention to this wild notion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.81,0:13:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,認為那不過是茲威基的又一個瘋狂的想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just another one of Zwicky's crazy ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們的太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,位於內圈的行星水星 它的移動速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the innermost planet, Mercury, moves much faster
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.25,0:13:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,要比最外圈的行星海王星快許多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than the outermost one, Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,聽上去這很順理成章 對不\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that makes sense, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,你越是用力推拉一個物體 它的速度也就越快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The harder you push or pull on something, the faster it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽的引力隨距離的增加而會減弱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun's gravity weakens with increasing distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.83,0:14:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 距離太陽更遠的行星移動得更慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so, the planets that are farther from the Sun move more slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,人們認為星系最外層的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everyone expected that the outermost stars in a galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.93,0:14:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,也應該是這樣移動的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would act the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的恆星都向著星系的中心集中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the stars are concentrated towards the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 它們的重力總和會牽引其它的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so, their collective gravity pulls on the other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,如同太陽牽引行星一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the same way the Sun pulls on the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.61,0:14:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,可是在1970年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But in the 1970s, when astronomer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,天文學家維拉·魯賓在研究僊女座星系時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vera Rubin studied the Andromeda Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.45,0:14:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,她發現這個星系的外層恆星並沒有遵循這個規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}she discovered that the outer stars obeyed no such rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它們與太陽系的外層行星不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unlike the outer planets of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.62,0:14:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,星系外層恆星的速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the outer stars in the galaxy were all going at the same speed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.36,0:14:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,與星系內層恆星的速度是一樣的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the stars that were closer in,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,它們移動得甚至比人們預想中的還要快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and they were moving way faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,"太有意思了" 維拉想道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"That's funny," Vera thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.77,0:14:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"僊女座星系里一定有古怪"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"There must be something weird about the Andromeda Galaxy."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,於是 她又觀測另一個星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So she looked at another galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.21,0:14:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,發現了同樣的現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Same story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,再下一個 也是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.81,0:15:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,維拉一共觀測了60個星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vera studied 60 galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.31,0:15:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,發現所有的星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and found that all of them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎都違背了萬有引力定律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}seemed to be violating the Law of Gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這是物理學中的核心理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a core principle of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,一開始 她的同事們對這個現象表示質疑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After some initial healthy skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.42,0:15:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後他們開始動手自己觀測\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}her colleagues looked for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.46,0:15:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,結果發現維拉的觀測結果是正確的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and found that Vera was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.76,0:15:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但並非是牛頓的萬有引力定律有問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's not that Isaac Newton had gotten the Law of Gravity wrong;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,而是維拉·魯賓發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vera Rubin had discovered that the gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,某種巨大而又不可見的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of something massive and invisible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,在迫使星星們移動加快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was forcing the stars to go fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.84,0:15:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,然後 有人想起了瘋狂的老茲威基的說法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then, someone remembered crazy old Fritz Zwicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,那不明來源的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the unknown source of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定是存在於星系團中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the galaxy clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,1933年的時候 他就將其稱之為"暗物質"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that he called "dark matter," back in 1933.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,維拉·魯賓證實了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vera Rubin had verified the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一個全新的 更遼闊的宇宙的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a new, much larger cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.10,0:15:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,它與我們過去以為很瞭解的那個宇宙一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And just like the one we thought we knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.37,0:15:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,充滿了奧秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it was filled with mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.44,0:16:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,暗物質完全是探測不到的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dark matter is completely unobservable,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.94,0:16:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,但它會產生引力效應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}except for its gravitational effect,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.71,0:16:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這會加速可見的恆星與星系的移動速度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which makes visible stars and galaxies move faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,它的性質同樣是一個謎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Its nature is another deep mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,魯賓提供的證據表明 這個不可見的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rubin had provided the evidence for an invisible universe
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.32,0:16:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,比我們已知的宇宙要大10倍以上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}nearly ten times more massive than the one we thought we knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.13,0:16:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,就好比暗夜裏站在海邊的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was as if we had been standing on the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,錯誤地認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at night, mistakenly believing
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.30,0:16:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,海浪上的小泡沫 就是大海的全部\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the froth on the waves was all there was to the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.15,0:16:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,維拉·魯賓觀測恆星時意識到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Vera Rubin looked at the stars and realized
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.78,0:16:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,眼前的星星只不過是海浪上的小泡沫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they were merely the foam on the waves,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,海洋最壯闊的部分 還不被人類知曉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that the greatest part of the ocean remained unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.56,0:16:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,且慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,這變得越來越瘋狂了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It gets crazier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的銀河系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.07,0:16:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,有數百億顆恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a few hundred billion stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.21,0:16:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,還有無數的星雲與塵埃\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}plus the clouds of gas and dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.71,0:16:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,那些東西過去曾是 未來也會再變為恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the stuff of once and future stars--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:17:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中還有上百億個其它星系--所有這些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and about a hundred billion other galaxies-- all of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.72,0:17:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上還沒統計進去的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including those uncounted billions of trillions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.99,0:17:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,數以億兆計的行星 衛星和彗星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of planets, moons, and comets--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.06,0:17:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的總和還只不過是這個宇宙的百分之五\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}amounts to only five percent of what is actually there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.16,0:17:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因為有個更大的未解之謎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because there's a bigger unsolved mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.33,0:17:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,比暗物質更神秘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than dark matter--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.37,0:17:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那就是暗能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dark energy, which makes up even more of the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,它佔據著大部分的宇宙並驅動著它的膨脹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and drives its expansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.67,0:17:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,弗裏茨•茲威基發現的超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it was Fritz Zwicky's supernovas
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,為人類揭示了一條顯示其存在的途徑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lit the way to the revelation of its existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.98,0:17:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,舉個例子 一顆恆星耗盡了它所有的核燃料後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In one scenario, a star consumes all of its nuclear fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它先是冷卻下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then cools,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.63,0:17:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,然後在自身引力的作用下突然塌縮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and suddenly collapses under its own gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,隨後在聚變的反作用力下恆星會發生巨大的爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The star rebounds in a massive explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,最後只遺留下一顆中子星或是一個黑洞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}leaving behind a neutron star or a black hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.57,0:17:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,由於爆發前那顆恆星的質量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Since the mass of the original star
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:17:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,上下浮動的區間很大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can fall within a wide range,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.84,0:17:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,它變為超新星後的峰值亮度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its peak brightness as a supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.41,0:18:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,也會有很大的不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can also vary widely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我們不能從亮度來判斷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, you can't tell how far away it is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.98,0:18:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這顆星星離我們有多遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just from how bright it looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆較近的超新星亮度看起來也許就會和在較遠地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A relatively nearby supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,爆發的超新星差不多 就算另一顆的爆發強度更大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}might appear just as bright as one that was more powerful, but farther away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.39,0:18:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.59,0:18:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,但還有另外一種超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's another kind of supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.52,0:18:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,它只有一種爆發強度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that comes in only one strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.59,0:18:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,它看上去彷彿就是激烈的探戈舞終曲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It marks the violent grand finale
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.93,0:18:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一顆紅巨星與一顆紅矮星翩翩共舞的宏大場景\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a tango danced by a giant star and a dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.43,0:18:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,當這兩顆星的運行軌道互相接近時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As the two stars orbit closely around each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,紅巨星外層的氣體會傾瀉而出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the giant sheds its outer layers of gas
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.74,0:18:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,流到紅矮星上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}onto the dwarf.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.74,0:18:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,當紅矮星增加的重量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When the added weight becomes too much
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.24,0:18:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,超過了它所能承受的極限時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for it to bear,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,星體就會像一顆巨大的核炸彈一樣爆炸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the dwarf detonates like a stupendous thermonuclear bomb.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.65,0:18:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,有持續好幾周的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For a few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.75,0:18:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,天空中這顆超新星的亮度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the brilliance of such a supernova rivals
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.39,0:18:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,會超過它的星系中其他恆星亮度的總和\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the combined light of all the stars in its galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,這種類型的超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This kind of supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.56,0:18:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,它們輸出的最大能量值是相同的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}always has the same maximum power output,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.10,0:18:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它大約比太陽亮50億倍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about five billion times brighter than our Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.90,0:19:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,通過巨大的天文望遠鏡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With big telescopes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.67,0:19:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以在非常遙遠的星系中看到它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we can see them in galaxies very far away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,即使它就位於可觀測宇宙的邊緣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}out toward the edge of the observable universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.35,0:19:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,因為所有這種類型的超新星具有相同的亮度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because all such supernovas have the same wattage,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.49,0:19:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 它們是用於測量距離的理想工具\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they're ideal tools for measuring distances
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.46,0:19:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,適用於宇宙中哪怕是最遙遠的星系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the farthest reaches of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.69,0:19:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我們也稱之為"標準燭光"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We call them "standard candles."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,1929年 埃德溫•哈勃發現宇宙正在膨脹\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1929, Edwin Hubble discovered that the universe is expanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.94,0:19:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,遙遠的星系正在遠離彼此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The distant galaxies are drifting away from one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.21,0:19:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,後來我們知道了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Later, we learned
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.88,0:19:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨脹始於140億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the expansion began some 14 billion years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.85,0:19:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,從"宇宙大爆炸" 開始的那一刻起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the explosive birth of the universe-- the big bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.99,0:19:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,人們曾以為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everybody assumed
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.05,0:19:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨脹速度會慢下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that the rate of expansion would be slowing down,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:19:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,這是由於宇宙各部分之間的引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}due to the mutual pull of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.22,0:19:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,互相牽引的結果\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between all the parts of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.99,0:20:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果有足夠多的暗物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If there is enough dark matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,它的引力最終會將宇宙的膨脹停止下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its gravity would eventually bring the expansion to a stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙又會縮回到原點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the universe would then fall back on itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.03,0:20:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,照這樣推理 宇宙中的萬物終究會在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In that case, everything would eventually collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.24,0:20:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,一次大擠壓中全面崩潰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a big crunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,但反過來說 如果宇宙中的暗物質再少一些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On the other hand, if the universe had less dark matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨脹就會永遠繼續下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the expansion would continue forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.51,0:20:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,只是速度會越來越慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just getting slower and slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.41,0:20:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,兩支互相競爭的天文學家團隊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Two competing teams of astronomers
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.02,0:20:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,同時在觀測著遙遠星系中的這些超新星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were observing those supernovas in distant galaxies.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.32,0:20:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,這可以說是另一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It turned out to be another one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.99,0:20:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,"有意思"的時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of those "that's funny" moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.42,0:20:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,1998年 這兩隻獨立的研究團隊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1998, both teams independently came
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.76,0:20:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,做出了同樣的結論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the same conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的膨脹不僅沒有減緩\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The expansion isn't slowing down at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.83,0:20:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,而且還在不停的加速\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's speeding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.60,0:20:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,這意味著宇宙會永遠膨脹下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This means the universe will continue to expand forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中似乎有一股神秘的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There seems to be a mysterious force in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.04,0:20:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,它的規模龐大得足以壓倒一切引力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that overwhelms gravity on the grandest scale
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,將宇宙分開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to push the cosmos apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.61,0:20:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中大部分的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of the energy of the universe is bound up
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.35,0:20:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,都被這股看不見的力量束縛著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in this unknown force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.85,0:21:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為"暗能量"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We call it "dark energy,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,可這個名字就和"暗物質"一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but that name, like "dark matter,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,我們不知道它是什麼 只能強給它起個名字而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is merely a code word for our ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我們承認不知道所有問題的答案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's okay not to know all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,承認自己的無知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's better to admit our ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,總比強行認可那些可能錯誤的答案好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than to believe answers that might be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.20,0:21:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,假裝自己什麼都懂 就是關上了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pretending to know everything closes the door
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,通往真相的大門\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to finding out what's really there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,今晚 我們的飛船航行到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Tonight, our ships sail
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,更奇異的水域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into even more exotic waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,跟我來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.62,0:21:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,人類只有兩艘飛船冒險進入了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only two of our ships have ventured
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.92,0:21:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,星際空間中的黑暗大洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the great dark ocean of interstellar space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.43,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這是史上最長的冒險之旅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The longest odyssey in all of history
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.30,0:21:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,它開始於1977年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was launched back in 1977--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.60,0:21:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,美國宇航局的旅行者1號與旅行者2號\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}NASA's Voyager 1 and 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.34,0:21:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,這兩艘飛船以每小時4萬英里的速度行進\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Voyagers move about 40,000 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:22:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它們讓人類得以第一次近距離觀察\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They gave us our first close-up look
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.51,0:22:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,木星上的大紅斑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at Jupiter's Great Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.58,0:22:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,那是比地球的尺寸還要大三倍的颶風\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a hurricane three times the size of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,其中一個颶風至少在1644年就已經開始刮起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and one that's been raging since at least 1644,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.46,0:22:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,並第一次被人類觀測到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when it was first observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.19,0:22:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我們知道 這些颶風至少可以延續數千年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For all we know, it could be thousands of years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號還發現了 在木星的衛星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Voyagers discovered the first active volcano
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.33,0:22:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,木衛一上有活火山的存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on another world, on Jupiter's moon Io...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.84,0:22:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,在木衛二的冰層下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and an ocean beneath the icy surface
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.01,0:22:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,則存在著海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the moon Europa...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.31,0:22:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,它可能擁有比地球至少多2倍的液態水\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with at least twice as much water as we have here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號還勇敢的飛越了土星環\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Voyagers dared to fly across Saturn's rings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.35,0:22:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,發現它是由數以百計的圓環帶組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and revealed that they were made of hundreds of thin bands
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.73,0:22:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,而這些圓環帶則是由小雪球組成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of orbiting snowballs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.90,0:22:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,在土星的巨大衛星土衛六上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On Saturn's giant moon Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.57,0:22:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號發現了比地球濃厚4倍的大氣層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager detected an atmosphere four times denser than Earth's.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.74,0:23:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,暗示著在土衛六上有可能存在甲烷的海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That hinted at the existence of hydrocarbon seas on Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.51,0:23:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,這一點後來被證實了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}which we later confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.15,0:23:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者2號讓人類第一次得到了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager 2 gave us our first portrait
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.15,0:23:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,最外層的行星 海王星的肖像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the outermost planet, Neptune...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.99,0:23:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,海王星上狂風咆哮 風速達每小時1000英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the winds roar at 1,000 miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.69,0:23:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,在它的衛星海衛一上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and its moon Triton, where geysers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.59,0:23:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,間歇泉能把沸騰的液氮噴到5英里高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of boiling nitrogen shoot five miles high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.23,0:23:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號成功的完成了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager successfully completed its mission of discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它對外層行星的觀測任務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the outer planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.91,0:23:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但它進入黑暗世界的冒險之旅\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but its odyssey into the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.91,0:23:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,才剛剛開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.21,0:23:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,在發射後的35年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}35 years after its launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.95,0:23:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者1號成為人類第一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager 1 became the first of our spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,進入未知領域的太空飛船\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to enter an uncharted realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.52,0:23:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽向各個方向不斷地發射出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun is constantly shooting out streams
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.76,0:23:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,帶電的粒子流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of charged particles in all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.09,0:23:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,粒子流的時速達100萬英里\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}moving at a million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:24:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是太陽風 它擴散後的區域是一個巨大的磁泡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This solar wind blows a vast magnetic bubble,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.20,0:24:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,形成了太陽風層 它一直延伸到最外層的行星之外\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our heliosphere, that extends beyond the outer planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.10,0:24:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,它把從星際空間進入的稀薄氣體向外推\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It pushes out against the thin gas of interstellar space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.47,0:24:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是一個世界的盡頭 另一個世界的起點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There's a border where one ends and the other begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.08,0:24:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者1號向地球報告說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager 1 reported back to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.25,0:24:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,它的探測器正在遭遇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that its detectors were being pummeled
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.78,0:24:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,越來越多的宇宙射線攻擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by more and more cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.32,0:24:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,直至現在 我們還是不知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Until then, we didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,哪裏才是浩瀚星際大洋的開始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where the interstellar ocean began.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.36,0:24:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者1號不斷前行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Voyager 1 pressed on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.63,0:24:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它穿越了人類從未穿越的邊界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}past a boundary we had never crossed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.86,0:24:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽風層為我們阻擋了大部分致命的宇宙射線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The heliosphere shields us from most of the deadly cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.73,0:24:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,當太陽風如驟雨般爆發時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When stormy solar winds blow,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.90,0:24:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽風層也會隨之擴張\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}this zone of protection grows;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.14,0:24:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽風平靜時 它會縮小\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in calm solar weather, it shrinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.27,0:24:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,當銀河系附近出現超新星爆發時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When a star goes supernova in our galactic neighborhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,爆發後的星體殘骸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the debris from the exploded star
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.65,0:24:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,會將太陽風層推向太陽的方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}pushes the heliosphere back towards the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,如果殘骸的能量足夠大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If it's strong enough to push it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.29,0:24:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,它就有可能會進入地球的軌道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all the way back to Earth's orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.22,0:25:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的星球就會沐浴在具有輻射性的超新星殘骸中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our planet gets a radioactive bath of supernova debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.29,0:25:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,好在這樣的情況不常發生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Luckily, this doesn't happen very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.13,0:25:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,最後一次出現是在200萬年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The last one was perhaps two million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.57,0:25:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,鄰近的一顆恆星爆發了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A neighboring star explodes a million years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.73,0:25:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上還要再過100萬年才會出現人類這個物種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}before there's even such a thing as the human species.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.41,0:25:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我們從何得知此事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How can we possibly know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.91,0:25:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,因為死亡的恆星會留下蹤跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Because the dying star left its traces
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.74,0:25:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,它就藏在海洋下幾英里處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}miles below the surface of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.25,0:25:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,這是錳結核 就像這塊小石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Manganese nodules, small rocks like this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.98,0:25:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,它分散在深海的海床上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are scattered over much of the deep sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.49,0:25:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,它的生長速度非常緩慢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They grow very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.33,0:25:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,100萬年才能長1毫米\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm talking a millimeter in a million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.10,0:25:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,一層層的堆疊生長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}layer upon layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,錳結核與細菌共生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These nodules grow in partnership with bacteria
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.17,0:25:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,它們吸取溶解在海水中的礦物質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by taking up minerals dissolved in the seawater.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.04,0:25:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,超新星會產生一種具有放射性的鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A supernova produces a radioactive form of iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.05,0:25:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,它和地球上自然產生的任何一種物質都不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}unlike anything made by natural processes on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.12,0:26:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,研究人員發現了這種鐵的痕跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Researchers found telltale traces of this iron
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.52,0:26:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,它就長在錳結核中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a thin layer below the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,外殼下的一個淺層裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the manganese nodules.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,研究人員把已知的錳結核的生長速率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They used the known rate of growth of the nodules
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.36,0:26:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,和每層的生長時間聯繫起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to date that layer and to connect it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.69,0:26:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,就能知道億萬年前恆星滅亡的命運了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the fate of a star that perished eons ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.33,0:26:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你看到的是石頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The difference between seeing nothing but a pebble
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.24,0:26:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但在科學家眼裏 這是深藏在裏面的宇宙的歷史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and reading the history of the cosmos inscribed inside it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.67,0:26:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是科學的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is science.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.25,0:26:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,星際大洋黑暗而深遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The interstellar ocean is dark and deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.25,0:26:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,從那裏看 太陽只不過是天空中一顆最亮的恆星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Out here, the Sun is just the brightest star in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.25,0:26:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號依然保持著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yet the Voyagers maintain their regular communications
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.69,0:26:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,與美國宇航局噴氣推進實驗室定期的聯繫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.86,0:26:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的交流要經過1光時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}talking back and forth across the light-hours
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.50,0:26:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是太空船與母港之間的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that separate these ships from their home port.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.40,0:26:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,再沒有人造的物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No other objects touched by human hands
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.24,0:26:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,曾如此冒險遠離家園\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have ever ventured this far from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.88,0:27:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,當這些飛船\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even after they lose their ability
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.38,0:27:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,失去了與人類通訊的能力之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to respond to our command,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.45,0:27:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號最後一個也是最長的一個任務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the last and, by far, the longest phase
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.68,0:27:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,就此拉開序幕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the Voyager mission will begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.63,0:27:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,1979年 當旅行者號繞著木星旋轉時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Back in 1979, when both Voyagers rounded Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.83,0:27:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,木星的巨大引力就像一個彈弓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its massive gravity acted as a slingshot,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.26,0:27:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,把它們拋出太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}flinging them out of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.27,0:27:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它們得以在銀河系的恆星間航行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to travel among the stars of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.47,0:27:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,時間是10億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.94,0:27:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,當年 卡爾•薩根意識到旅行者號的任務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carl Sagan recognized that the Voyager mission
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.61,0:27:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,為人類提供了兩張接近永恆的機票\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}offered two free tickets to something approaching eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.68,0:27:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,他組建了一個小隊 創造了一些信息\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He assembled a small team to create a message
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.68,0:27:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,以便在未來的某一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to any civilization that might, one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,當某個文明遇到這個廢棄的航天器時可以讀到它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}encounter the derelict spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.29,0:27:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,26個世紀前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}26 centuries ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.49,0:27:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,亞述國王以撒哈頓寫道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Assyrian king Esarhaddon wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.33,0:27:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"朕以青銅鑄碑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}"I had monuments made of bronze
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.10,0:27:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,銘文於泥版\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and inscriptions of baked clay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.77,0:28:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,遺之於基石 傳之於後世"\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I left them in the foundations for future times."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.17,0:28:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,這些象形圖形延續了這一古老的傳統\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These hieroglyphics continue that ancient tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.51,0:28:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它們被刻印在蓋子上 上面的信息被設計成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They are inscribed on the cover of a message designed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.51,0:28:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,方便其它世界或後世的生物閱讀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to be read by the beings of other worlds and times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.65,0:28:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我們人類與外星文明之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What could we possibly have in common
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.22,0:28:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,有可能會有什麼共同點呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with an alien civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.69,0:28:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,他們會有自己與眾不同的進化史\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with its own separate evolutionary history
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.39,0:28:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至有可能比我們更先進\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and one so far advanced beyond us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.66,0:28:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,能自由遨遊於星際空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that they can patrol interstellar space?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.90,0:28:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,但至少有一樣東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}One thing at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.46,0:28:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,是宇宙間通用的語言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a universal language...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.23,0:28:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,科學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}science.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.07,0:28:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,引力的束縛是很難被打破的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's hard to break the bonds of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.07,0:28:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,想要在宇宙之海中暢遊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can only sail the cosmic seas
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.34,0:28:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你必須通曉數學與物理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if you speak mathematics and physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.71,0:28:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,氫是宇宙中最常見的元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hydrogen is the most common element in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.81,0:28:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,氫原子中的電子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The electron in a hydrogen atom
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.82,0:28:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在它的旋轉方向上作翻轉運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}flips the direction of its spin
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.65,0:28:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它的速率或頻率是恆定的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at a constant rate, or frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.65,0:28:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,氫原子就像是個迷你的天然時鐘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hydrogen atoms are like tiny natural clocks--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.66,0:28:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,滴…答…走動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tick... tock.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.49,0:29:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這就意味著我們與外星人共同擁有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now we have a unit of time in common
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.69,0:29:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,相同的一個時間單位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.33,0:29:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,瞭解了這個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This will come in handy when we get to the next level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.23,0:29:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,再轉到下一個信息時就好理解了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.83,0:29:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,下面的信息是指示出我們在宇宙中的位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Here's our return address in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.44,0:29:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,脈衝星是快速旋轉的中子星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pulsars are rapidly-spinning neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.27,0:29:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,它們會發出定期爆發的無線電波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that give off regular bursts of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.41,0:29:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以根據這個來設定時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can set your clock by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.11,0:29:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽位於這個示意圖的中心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun is at the center of this diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.71,0:29:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這些線條指向14顆最近的脈衝星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the lines point to the 14 nearest pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.38,0:29:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,有一個簡單的標籤指示出了每顆脈衝星的特有頻率\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A simple code labels each pulsar with its unique frequency,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,並用氫原子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}using the ticktock of the hydrogen atom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.39,0:29:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,作為計時單位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as the unit of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.13,0:29:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 外星的天文學家能利用這張示意圖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So alien astronomers could use this diagram
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.96,0:29:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,來定位出旅行者號航天器的母星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to locate the home star of the Voyager spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.56,0:29:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在我們銀河系中的位置\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.20,0:29:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他們還能知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They could also tell
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.80,0:29:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,這艘航天器已經發射多久了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how long ago the spacecraft was launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.87,0:29:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這一點很重要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that's important because the Voyager record
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.07,0:29:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,因為旅行者號的外殼設計壽命是10億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}has a projected shelf life of 1,000 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.11,0:29:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,就想像一下你是一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Become an extraterrestrial archaeologist
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.75,0:29:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,外星球的考古學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.75,0:29:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,有一架人造航天器完成了它在星際大洋中的使命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An artifact has been fished out of the interstellar ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.09,0:30:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它是由外星智慧生命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was made by beings
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.62,0:30:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,在10億年前建造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that lived about a billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.79,0:30:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你要怎樣通過它瞭解他們和他們的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What would you make of them and their world?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.16,0:30:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他們給我們送來了他們的音樂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've sent us their music
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.90,0:30:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,還有用59種人類語言說出的問候方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and greetings in 59 human languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.87,0:30:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這是地球上一位小孩子向你打招呼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Hello from the children of planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.04,0:30:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,鯨魚的語言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And one whale language.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.14,0:30:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,還有一串聲音的組合 包括土星五號火箭發射的聲音\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And a sound essay that includes a Saturn V rocket launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.35,0:30:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,一位母親對她新生的嬰兒說的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A mother's first words to her newborn baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.69,0:30:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,哦 來吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oh, come on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.99,0:30:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,做個好孩子…做個好孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Be a good boy... be a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.16,0:30:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,一位剛剛墜入愛河的年輕女子的腦波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The brain waves of a young woman newly fallen in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.96,0:30:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,還有脈衝星的聲音\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And the sound of a pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.64,0:30:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,所有這些都能存在10億年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All of that will live for a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.02,0:31:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,10億年有多久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How long is a billion years?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.79,0:31:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你能把創世大爆炸以來的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you compress all the time since the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.03,0:31:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是宇宙誕生的那一刻開始的時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the explosive birth of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.03,0:31:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,壓縮成一個地球年的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into a single Earth year,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.03,0:31:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,10億年就相當於這1年中的1個月\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a billion years is about one month of that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.37,0:31:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,10億年前的地球上發生了些什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What was happening on Earth a billion years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.74,0:31:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,大部分的地球陸地都聚集在一個超大陸上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Most of Earth's land was amassed into a supercontinent
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.78,0:31:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,我們稱之為羅迪尼亞大陸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}called Rodinia.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.48,0:31:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個荒地 沒有動物 沒有植物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a barren desert-- no animals, no plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.15,0:31:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,10億年前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A billion years ago, there wasn't enough oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.12,0:31:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣裏沒有足夠的氧以形成臭氧層\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in our atmosphere to form an ozone layer,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.56,0:31:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有它的保護\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and without it, ultraviolet radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.22,0:31:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,紫外線會阻止生命在陸地上生存\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}prevented life from colonizing the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.96,0:31:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,羅迪尼亞大陸看上去可能更像火星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Rodinia probably looked more like Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,而不像今天的地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than present-day Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.23,0:32:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大的海洋世界產生大暴雨\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The giant world ocean produced huge rainstorms
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.97,0:32:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,造成洪水和侵蝕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}causing flooding and erosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.50,0:32:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,冰川形成 它們緩慢而無情的運動著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Glaciers formed, and their slow but relentless movements
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.64,0:32:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,把陸地塑造成新的樣子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}carved the land into new shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.84,0:32:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,單細胞的生物主宰著海洋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Single-celled organisms dominated the oceans,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.25,0:32:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,被稱為"微生物席"的生物集群地已經開始出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but some existed in colonies called "microbial mats,"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.85,0:32:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,第一個多細胞生物很快會演變形成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the first multicellular organisms would soon evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.59,0:32:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,10億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And a billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.59,0:32:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,今天的地球又會變成怎樣…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what will Earth be like...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.59,0:32:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的城市 埃及的金字塔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}long after our cities, the Egyptian pyramids,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.26,0:32:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,洛基山脈 是否早已被侵蝕為塵土\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the Rocky Mountains have all been eroded to dust?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.43,0:32:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,對於這麼久遠的時間來說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are few things we can say with confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我們沒有幾件事是可以說得清的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}about such a far distant time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我們唯一可以肯定的是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The only thing we can say for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.21,0:32:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我們所認識的地球會發生巨變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is that Earth as we know it will be so changed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.05,0:32:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,幾乎沒有人會認得出 這曾經是我們的家園\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that we would scarcely recognize it as home.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.38,0:32:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但就算是10億年後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But even a thousand million years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.95,0:33:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我們人類的本性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}something of who we were and the music that we made
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.49,0:33:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,和我們在久遠的春天寫下的音樂\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in that long-ago spring...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.79,0:33:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,都會延續下去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}will live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.67,0:33:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在如此遙遠的未來 我們的太陽系\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In that distant future, our Sun will have completed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.87,0:33:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,完成了繞著銀河系中心公轉4圈的歷程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}another four orbits around the center of the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.52,0:33:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號早已飛到了遠離太陽的領域\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}...and the Voyagers will have ventured far from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.36,0:33:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾•薩根曾是旅行者號影像小組的一員\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carl Sagan was a member of Voyager's imaging team,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.09,0:33:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,旅行者號拍攝的最後一張照片來自於他的想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and it was his idea that Voyager take one last picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,在一代人以前\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A generation before,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.37,0:33:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,阿波羅登月飛行的最後一位宇航員\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an astronaut on the last Apollo flight to the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.24,0:33:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,照下了一張地球的全景照片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had taken a picture of the whole Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.90,0:33:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個沒有邊界的行星\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the planet as a world without borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.11,0:33:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,它成了一種新意識的象徵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It became an icon of a new consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.51,0:33:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,卡爾實現了這個過程的下一步\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Carl realized the next step in this process.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.68,0:34:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他說服了美國宇航局把旅行者一號的鏡頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He convinced NASA to turn the Voyager 1 camera
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.75,0:34:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在飛過海王星時 轉回地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}back towards Earth when the spacecraft went beyond Neptune
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.56,0:34:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,讓它最後看一眼家園 他所說的那個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for one last look homeward at what he called...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.23,0:34:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,泛著蒼白藍光的小點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the pale blue dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.04,0:34:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.64,0:34:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,那是家園\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.20,0:34:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.81,0:34:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,在那裏 你愛的每個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}On it, everyone you love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,你認識的每個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}everyone you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.58,0:34:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,你聽說過的每個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}everyone you ever heard of,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.58,0:34:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,在這世上存在過的每個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every human being who ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.25,0:34:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,度過了自己的一生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lived out their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,聚集在這裏的 是我們的歡樂和痛苦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The aggregate of our joy and suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.42,0:34:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,是成千上萬的宗教信仰 意識形態\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}thousands of confident religions, ideologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.26,0:34:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,和經濟學說\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and economic doctrines,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.26,0:34:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,每個獵手與覓食者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every hunter and forager,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.43,0:34:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,每個英雄與懦夫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every hero and coward,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.43,0:34:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,每個文明的創立者和毀滅者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every creator and destroyer of civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.90,0:34:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,每個國王與農夫\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every king and peasant,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.90,0:34:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,每對年輕的愛侶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every young couple in love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.94,0:34:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,每一個母親與父親 充滿希望的孩子們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every mother and father, hopeful child,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.24,0:34:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,發明家與探險家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}inventor and explorer,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.51,0:35:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,每一位高尚的教師 每一位貪腐的政客\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every teacher of morals, every corrupt politician,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.18,0:35:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,每一位超級明星 每一位最高領袖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every superstar, every supreme leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.29,0:35:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,人類史上的每一位聖人和罪人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every saint and sinner in the history of our species,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.16,0:35:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,都生活在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}lived there...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.16,0:35:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如一粒微塵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on a mote of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.99,0:35:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,懸浮在一束陽光之中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}suspended... in a sunbeam.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.26,0:35:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,地球是在浩瀚的宇宙背景下的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth is a very small stage
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.50,0:35:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,一個很小的舞台\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in a vast, cosmic arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.34,0:35:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,想想過去的血流成河\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of the rivers of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.61,0:35:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,那為帝王將相而流的血\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}spilled by all those generals and emperors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.34,0:35:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,只為讓他們在光榮和勝利中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that in glory and triumph
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.81,0:35:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,成為瞬間的偉人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they could become the momentary masters
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.78,0:35:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,佔有那一個小點中…那一小部分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of a fraction... of a dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.05,0:35:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,想想那無盡的殘酷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think of the endless cruelties visited
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.19,0:35:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,圖像裏那一個像素點的某個角落的民眾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the inhabitants of one corner of this pixel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.69,0:35:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,每天把這殘酷施加到與他們沒什麼區別的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on the scarcely distinguishable inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.63,0:35:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,另一個角落的民眾身上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of some other corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.73,0:35:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他們為何常常誤解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How frequent their misunderstandings,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.80,0:35:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,他們為何渴望殺死對方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how eager they are to kill one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.80,0:36:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,他們的憎恨為何如此狂熱\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how fervent their hatreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.14,0:36:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我們在裝模做樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our posturings,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.68,0:36:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我們自以為很重要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}our imagined self-importance,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.75,0:36:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,妄想著我們人類地位特殊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the delusion that we have some privileged position
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.35,0:36:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,在宇宙中與眾不同\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.98,0:36:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,這一切 都因這泛著蒼白藍光的小點而動搖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are challenged by this point of pale light.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.69,0:36:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的星球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.72,0:36:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,不過是一粒孤獨的微塵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a lonely speck in the great,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.76,0:36:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,籠罩在偉大的宇宙黑暗之中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}enveloping cosmic dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.86,0:36:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,我們默默無聞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In our obscurity,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.70,0:36:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,沉浸在無盡的浩瀚裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in all this vastness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.50,0:36:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有一絲線索顯示 除了我們自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there is no hint that help will come from elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.24,0:36:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,還有誰能拯救我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to save us from ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,地球是目前已知唯一有生命的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.45,0:36:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,生命再無其他去處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is nowhere else,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.45,0:36:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,至少在不久的將來 亦是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at least in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.45,0:36:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有外星球 供人類遷移\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to which our species could migrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,只可參觀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Visit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.06,0:36:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,不能定居\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Settle, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.29,0:36:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,不管你喜歡與否\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Like it or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:37:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 只有地球供我們立足\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the moment, the Earth is where we make our stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.93,0:37:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,據說研習天文 可以讓人謙卑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It has been said that astronomy is a humbling
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.27,0:37:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,塑造人心 磨煉個性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and character-building experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.41,0:37:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,也許再沒有更好的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There is perhaps no better demonstration
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.91,0:37:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,能比這遙遠的畫面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the folly of human conceits
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.78,0:37:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,更好地顯示出人類的自負與愚蠢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than this distant image.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.32,0:37:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,對我而言 它強調了我們的責任\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}To me, it underscores our responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.92,0:37:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,要對人更友善\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to deal more kindly with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.62,0:37:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,懂得珍惜與愛護\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to preserve and cherish
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.12,0:37:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這泛著蒼白藍光的小點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the pale blue dot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.29,0:37:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,是我們知道的唯一的家園\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the only home we've ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.34,0:37:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是如何\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.34,0:37:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,在這一粒微塵上居住的渺小生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tiny creatures living on that speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.74,0:37:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,是如何千方百計地把宇宙飛船\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ever manage to figure out how to send spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.08,0:37:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,送入銀河的星星之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}out among the stars of the Milky Way?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.91,0:37:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,就在幾百年前 也就是宇宙歷中的幾秒時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Only a few centuries ago, a mere second of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們尚不知道自己身在何方 時為何時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we knew nothing of where or when we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.95,0:37:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,對宇宙的其他部分一無所知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Oblivious to the rest of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.76,0:38:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我們身居囚籠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we inhabited a kind of prison--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.36,0:38:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,活在自己的小宇宙裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a tiny universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.36,0:38:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,困在堅殼之中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}bounded by a nutshell.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.97,0:38:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我們是如何逃出囚籠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How did we escape from the prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,是因為世世代代探索者的不懈努力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the work of generations of searchers
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.21,0:38:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,他們發自內心地遵從5條簡單規則\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}who took five simple rules to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.95,0:38:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,質疑權威\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Question authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.95,0:38:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不輕信人言\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No idea is true just because someone says so,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.29,0:38:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,包括自己在內\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.96,0:38:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,獨立思考\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Think for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.23,0:38:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,自我質疑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Question yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.57,0:38:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,不因自己想要相信 而相信任何事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Don't believe anything just because you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.24,0:38:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,相信不代表能成為現實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Believing something doesn't make it so.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.04,0:38:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,依靠觀察與實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Test ideas by the evidence gained
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.04,0:38:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,以實證檢驗想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from observation and experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.75,0:38:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,如果自己喜歡的想法沒有通過全面的檢驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If a favorite idea fails a well-designed test,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.15,0:39:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是錯的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.35,0:39:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,樂觀一點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.99,0:39:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,遵循證據 無論它指向哪裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Follow the evidence, wherever it leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.43,0:39:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,如果沒有證據 不妄下定論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If you have no evidence, reserve judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.86,0:39:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,也許最重要的規則就是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And perhaps the most important rule of all...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.93,0:39:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,要記住 你也會犯錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Remember, you could be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.70,0:39:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是最優秀的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even the best scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.44,0:39:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,也曾經在某些事情上犯錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}have been wrong about some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.37,0:39:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓 愛因斯坦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton, Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.11,0:39:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,還有歷史上每一位偉大的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and every other great scientist in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.88,0:39:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他們都犯過錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they all made mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.38,0:39:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,這很正常 是人都會犯錯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of course they did-- they were human.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.59,0:39:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,科學讓我們不再欺騙自己\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science is a way to keep from fooling ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.92,0:39:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,欺騙別人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家們有罪嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Have scientists known sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.23,0:39:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,有的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.73,0:39:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我們曾濫用科學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We have misused science, just as we have
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.10,0:39:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,就像手邊的工具一樣隨意使用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}every other tool at our disposal,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.37,0:39:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我們不能把科學\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and that's why we can't afford
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.57,0:39:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,放在少數的掌權者手中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to leave it in the hands of a powerful few.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.54,0:40:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,當科學更多的屬於全人類時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The more science belongs to all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,它就越不會被亂用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the less likely it is to be misused.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.79,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,科學的價值能阻止\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}These values undermine the appeals
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.46,0:40:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,狂熱與無知\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of fanaticism and ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.76,0:40:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,畢竟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.66,0:40:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙的大部分是黑暗的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the universe is mostly dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.13,0:40:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,只有點點的星光點綴著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}dotted by islands of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.40,0:40:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,瞭解了地球的年齡 恆星的距離\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Learning the age of the Earth or the distance to the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.07,0:40:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,生命的演變\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or how life evolves--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.07,0:40:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,這會讓世界有什麼區別\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}what difference does that make?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.34,0:40:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯 這取決於\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well, part of it depends on how big a universe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.08,0:40:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,你願意生活在多大的宇宙裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you're willing to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.98,0:40:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,有些人喜歡小宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some of us like it small.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.98,0:40:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,沒關係\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.61,0:40:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,完全可以理解\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.02,0:40:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但我喜歡大的宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But I like it big.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.75,0:40:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,當我把這一切放在我的心裏 我的腦海裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when I take all of this into my heart and my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.92,0:40:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我會感到心情振奮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm uplifted by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.86,0:40:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,當這種感覺涌起 我希望看到它是真實的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And when I have that feeling, I want to know that it's real,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.66,0:40:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,而不僅僅是我腦海中的想像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that it's not just something happening inside my own head,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.16,0:40:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因為這就是真相\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}because it matters what's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.33,0:40:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,而我們的想像\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and our imagination is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.80,0:41:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,與自然中令人驚嘆的現實相比 根本不算什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}compared with Nature's awesome reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.31,0:41:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要知道 在那黑暗的地方有什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to know what's in those dark places,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.35,0:41:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,在創世大爆炸之前發生了什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and what happened before the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.12,0:41:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要知道 在宇宙的視界之外是什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to know what lies beyond the cosmic horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.99,0:41:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,生命又是如何起源的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and how life began.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.89,0:41:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中有沒有個地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Are there other places in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.39,0:41:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,物質和能量在那裏被賦予\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where matter and energy have become alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,生命和意識\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and aware?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.87,0:41:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要瞭解我們的先祖\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to know my ancestors--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.08,0:41:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,瞭解他們每一個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要成為一個美好而強大的聯接\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to be a good, strong link
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.85,0:41:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,聯繫世世代代的人類\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the chain of generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.75,0:41:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要保護我的孩子們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want to protect my children
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.58,0:41:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,以及未來的子孫後代\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the children of ages to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.75,0:41:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我們 代表著宇宙在這個世界的耳目\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We, who embody the local eyes and ears
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.96,0:41:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,代表著宇宙在這個世界的想法與情感\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and thoughts and feelings of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.69,0:41:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,我們開始瞭解人類的起源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we've begun to learn the story of our origins--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.96,0:42:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,思考繁星的故事 物質的演化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}star stuff contemplating the evolution of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.87,0:42:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,追溯意識起源之前那條漫長的道路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tracing that long path by which it arrived at consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.57,0:42:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們與這個星球上的其他生物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We and the other living things on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,攜帶著宇宙進化的遺產\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}carry a legacy of cosmic evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.78,0:42:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,逾越了數十億年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}spanning billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.21,0:42:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們將這些知識銘記於心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If we take that knowledge to heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.45,0:42:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們瞭解並熱愛大自然的本質\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we come to know and love nature as it really is,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.98,0:42:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的子孫們一定會記住我們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}then we will surely be remembered by our descendants
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.05,0:42:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我們是生命之鏈中美好而強大的一環\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as good, strong links in the chain of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.16,0:42:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的子孫們也會繼續這神聖的探索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And our children will continue this sacred searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.49,0:42:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,薪火相傳 不斷開拓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}seeing for us as we have seen for those who came before,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.26,0:42:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,就在這宇宙之中 發現我們做夢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}discovering wonders yet undreamt of...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.57,0:42:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,都想不到的奇跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.77,0:43:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an5\pos(193,145)\fad(500,500)}{\3c&HFFFFFF&\fscy1800\fscx3400\c&H000000&\bord1\shad0}■
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.77,0:43:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an5\fad(800,800)\fs18\pos(193,145)\fn方正小标宋_GBK\c&HFFFFFF&\bord0\shad0\b1}在製作這部紀錄片的字幕的過程中\n越來越發現人類的渺小至極\n世界永遠超出我們所想像的\n總括而言 智慧 勇氣 倔強 都是科研人員必須擁有的特質\n而這部紀錄片最後的那一段\n也向大家作出了在科學世界探索的五大要素\n這部紀錄片比你們書本上學到的東西還要多\n儘管今天我們無法發掘到宇宙的全部奧妙\n希望這部紀錄片能夠激發你\n相信某一天 坐在螢幕前的你 特別是還年輕的你們\n在未來將會能夠為我們解開謎團 為人類發展揭開全新的一頁
